Automatic Commercial License

This document outlines the terms for obtaining a commercial license for Automatic.

Purpose

A commercial license grants rights beyond the Business Source License (BUSL), including:
- Unlimited users within a single organization
- Commercial distribution and resale rights
- SaaS deployment and hosting rights
- White-label and embedding rights (negotiable)
- Priority support access (negotiable)

Eligibility

Commercial licenses are available for:
- Organizations with more than ten (10) concurrent users
- Companies wishing to distribute Automatic as part of a commercial product
- SaaS providers hosting Automatic for customers
- Partners requiring redistribution rights

Pricing

License pricing is based on:
- Number of users or seats
- Deployment model (on-premise, cloud, embedded)
- Redistribution scope

Contact for current pricing.

How to Obtain

1. Contact: licenses@automatic.dev
2. Provide:
   - Organization name and contact
   - Intended use case (internal, SaaS, redistribution, etc.)
   - Estimated user count
   - Deployment environment

3. Receive a commercial license agreement tailored to your use case.

For Enterprises

Enterprise licenses include:
- Unlimited users within your organization
- Indemnification protection
- Custom terms and SLAs
- Dedicated support channels

Contact: enterprise@automatic.dev

